properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of severe thunderstorms which may produce tornadoes. Intense thunderstorms have developed over parts of southern Saskatchewan. There is a potential for isolated tornadoes for the remainder of the afternoon and into the early evening hours. These thunderstorms are also capable of producing very large hail, strong winds, and torrential downpours. ### This is a dangerous and potentially life-threatening situation. Tornado watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce tornadoes. properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of severe thunderstorms that may be capable of producing strong wind gusts, large hail and heavy rain. Thunderstorms will continue to move in from Saskatchewan this afternoon or evening. Some of these thunderstorms may be severe. The risk of severe thunderstorms will exist for this afternoon and tonight. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.
Expires: 2019-07-08T08:29:57-00:00

properties.Title: Tornado Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 5:53 p.m. MDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm that is possibly producing a tornado. Damaging winds, large hail and locally intense rainfall are also possible. The thunderstorm is located 2 km west of Lomond and is moving to the east at 35 km/h. Communities in the path include: Lomond ### This is a dangerous and potentially life-threatening situation. Tornado warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing tornadoes.
